
DEPENDENCIES
------------

Agar requires the Software DirectMedia Layer (http://www.libsdl.org) as
well as the FreeType library (http://www.freetype.org).

Optionally, Agar may be compiled with OpenGL support (--with-gl).

INSTALLATION
------------

1) Execute the configure script (see ./configure --help for options).
   $ ./configure

   To perform a concurrent build, use the --srcdir option. A concurrent build
   in a memory filesystem mounted directory can speed up the build drastically.
   $ cd /path/to/builddir
   $ /path/to/sourcedir/configure --srcdir=/path/to/sourcedir [...]

2) Build dependencies with the depend target.
   $ make depend

3) Compile the library, binaries, archives (and man pages if nroff(1) is there).
   $ make

4) Install the library, binaries, data files and manual pages. If prefix
   is /usr/local, /usr/local/share/agar/man should be registered with man(1).
   # make install

   Alternatively, if you are hacking the agar source, invoke the `links'
   target in the application's directory to create ~/.cave symbolic links
   to data files inside the source tree.
   $ cd ./cave && make links

6) Execute the game by running `cave'.
   $ cave

   The level editor (if compiled in), is invoked with the -e flag.
   $ cave -e

